The only accepted means of added protection on historic furniture is wax,
a good quality blend of beeswax and carnauba, preferably in an emulsion
form.
Proper use of the materials is highly recommended.
Daily maintanence should only consist of dusting in which Endust is
recommended.
The person who said that lemon oil was a godsend because of wax has merely
created what we call the &quot;illusion of gloss&quot;, the oil has masked the
improperly applied wax,
